time-range_schema.description: Specify a time range. It includes periodic time ranges within one week and absolute time ranges. These time ranges determine application validity.

name.description: Specify the name of a time range. To avoid ambiguity, do not use the name 'all'.

status.description: Identify whether the time range is valid.

absolute-ranges.description: List of all absolute time ranges.

absolute-range.description: Specify the period of time, which is not cyclic and has no cycle.

start-time.description: Specify the start time and date. The start time must be earlier than the end time.

end-time.description: Specify the end time and date. The end time must be later than the start time.

period-ranges.description: List of all periodic time ranges.

period-range.description: Specify the period of time taken by a cycle, which is cyclic.

day-of-week.description: Specify the day on which a configured time range is valid.

start-time.description: Specify the start time of a time range.

end-time.description: Specify the end time of a time range.
